1.title: Trust Me
1.plot: The mystery of Sally's case deepens as Sally does her first hypno-regression with Milgram. Office politics continue as Robinette calculates his plan and Dr. Wellman informs Milgram about the mass in Sally's head. Two young ladies, Alphane and Lily are moving from New York to Baltimore, while their mother, Broadway star Whit Wilkerson, worries about their future.

2.title: Nothing Is Sacred When You're Asleep
2.plot: Joe can't figure out what's going on in the apartment next door, while Lily and Alphane arrive in Baltimore wondering how it will compare to New York. Dean Savage, PI, goes back to his home town in New York and meets Chick D'Onfrio and Bobby Leone, "friends" from the old neighborhood. Sally and Milgram go deeper into her dreams revealing what happens to her in the night. Sister Maria reveals herself to be more than a nun as she leaves the convent in New York for Baltimore. Pepper and Lisa Hill tryst even as Lisa angles for her next career move. Elizabeth stops her car...

3.title: I Know More Than Most People Don't Know
3.plot: Maria arrives in Baltimore. Joe's eavesdropping on his neighbors' apartment has him concerned, as Sally appears and enters the apartment. Kevin has a choice to make when confronted by Claire Tighlman, his eccentric investment advisor. For Dr. Milgram, hospital politics become more complex as Dr. Steck makes an announcement, while Dr. Robinette's secret meeting in the parking garage turns bad.

4.title: It's in the Blood
4.plot: Lily and Alphane look for an apartment in Baltimore and meet Alphane's "old friend" Solix. Whit and Teddy rehearse The Cherry Orchard at Whit's apartment. Mob boss Bobby Leone is uncomfortable when he can't call the shots in his meeting with the mysterious Colonel Strong. Milgram and Evelyn's unease is now palpable as they talk around key issues. Sally never makes it to a movie date with Mimi and David because of a run-in with The Man In The Brimmed Hat. It triggers her deeper memories of what is going on during her nighttime alien abductions.

5.title: What Are You, a UN Observer or Something..?
5.plot: Claire's temper is ignited at the local pub, while the abductees hold a meeting full of internal dissent. Evelyn continues to prepare for her work with Mrs. McClintock. Milgram and Robinette discuss Milgram's riffing on his case load in a tense conversation, and Lisa Hill does her first hypno-regression session. Sally's life is now almost wholly consumed by various alien interactions as she moves to her wit's edge.

6.title: Sunflowers
6.plot: Claire's many sides clarify as she begins her day in a fog. Lisa Hill does her first hypo-regression session with Dr. Milgram as Susie finds Joe in the hallway. Sally's trip to Columbus to try the Rabin case is interrupted by a phone call, a visitor and a sudden stop. Milgram faces a new hall of mirrors as he tries to process the past two days.

1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Sally Lemm works another late night on a big upcoming litigation. She is interrupted by dogs barking and a commotion in the backyard. She goes to investigate.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: Dr. Milgram is given a prestigious international award for his work but he and Evelyn disagree about its implications. Sally has returned from the yard. Not good.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Dr. Milgram may be slacking off on the job as Evelyn's "issues" get worse.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Sally and her boyfriend Paul Melchior meet in the park. Later in the day Sally and her best friend Mimi Hallen and Mimi's boyfriend David King have coffee.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Milgram, now doing book-signings for his Pullman Prize-winning book, is approached by David King who urges him to see Sally and help her with her problems. Dr. Peter Steck, Milgrams line boss, isn't happy when Milgram gets back to the office, confronting him on Dr. Robinette's concerns about Milgram's handling of the Patient Reiss case.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Sally, preparing for the Rabin case, the biggest in her career, finds fault with Susie Kramer's prep work, while puzzled Bix Strong, Sally's boss, eavesdrops. David King calls Sally and recommends the name of a psychiatrist she could consult about her sleep loss. Work pressures trigger flashbacks Sally can't comprehend, and she leaves her office to re-compose, only to fall deeper into recollection of a significant past event in her life.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Sally comes out of her flashback disoriented, as Steck challenges Milgram on his new patient, who will be making her first visit that day. Distracted by office administration, Dr. Milgram is taken by surprise as his assistant Pam users in new client Sally Lemm, who doesn't "really want to be here..." Off to a rocky start, Milgram and Sally begin to discuss her issues, but are interrupted by a surprise visit from Dr. Steck. After her first visit, Sally surprises Milgram by handing him some papers, and telling him she thinks something weird is going on.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: A woman named Dana McCall bumps into Dr. Milgram and requests an appointment, as Dr. Steck and Dr. Finlayson review Milgram's recent job performance. Later, Milgram and Evelyn enjoy some much-needed time together at a restaurant near the bay. Meanwhile Sally meets with Dean Savage, Private Investigator. Savage is curious about her interest in Milgram, on whom she is having him do background research. Sally's boss Bix, impatient with her recent distractions, interrupts their meeting. He needs her to get over to see the client whose huge case they will litigate in a few...

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: Evelyn hosts a dinner party for close friends Neurosurgeon Dr. Liz Wellman and her husband Art Critic Warren Shipley. Coming from the office Dan is late for the party. Simmering Evelyn confronts him at the dinner when Dan explains his new-found interest in UFOs.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Milgram and Sally meet to discuss the results of her head X-rays. Dana McCall has a meeting with Pepper Redfeld that reveals what she is up to and learns she has a new assistant, Rick Lake.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Sally, Bix and lawyers prep for the big trial in Columbus. Bix warns Sally afterward that she seems out of focus.Later, UFO experiencers meet, Sally and Lisa among them. After, Lisa explores Sally's feelings about the meeting.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: Susie Kramer and Joe Courson Noori leave their apartment and bump into their strange new neighbors. Susie stops at Birdie's Cafe for her morning coffee, where several Oxford Hospital doctors, Bix, Pepper, Dean Savage, PI and others mingle as they start their day.

-1.title: Prologue
-1.plot: Dr. Daniel Milgram looks back at what happened with Sally, between he and Evelyn, and wonders about the way forward.

imdb.plot outline: The story of an internationally prominent doctor, Daniel Milgram, who inadvertently becomes a detective when new client corporate lawyer Sally Lemm, comes to him at wits end. Her case plunges them both deeply into the dark world of UFOs. The truth is . . . No one is prepared for alien presence.
imdb.title: Milgram and the Fastwalkers
plot: World-class psychiatrist treats corporate lawyer and ends up investigating alien presence and UFOs.::Richard Cutting
